00:21:59,986 --> 00:22:02,687
lovely girl.

267
00:22:02,689 --> 00:22:05,623
And your mother
loves you

268
00:22:05,625 --> 00:22:09,493
so very, very much.

269
00:22:10,797 --> 00:22:12,663
She loves you

270
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:15,966
because you are perfect.

271
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:18,769
Absolutely...

272
00:22:18,771 --> 00:22:20,338
Perfect.

273
00:22:21,741 --> 00:22:23,974
You really
should eat, dear.

274
00:22:36,756 --> 00:22:38,522
[GASPS]

275
00:22:39,926 --> 00:22:41,625
[SIGHS]

276
00:22:41,627 --> 00:22:43,627
What did you say to me?

277
00:22:48,067 --> 00:22:52,069
Just once I would like
to have a nice dinner

278
00:22:52,071 --> 00:22:55,039
without you
picking a fight with me.

279
00:22:57,076 --> 00:23:01,078
You always
find some way

280
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:03,614
to ruin my appetite.

281
00:23:03,616 --> 00:23:06,450
Maybe next time
you can make the dinner

282
00:23:06,452 --> 00:23:07,952
and I'll berate
your cooking skills.

283
00:23:07,954 --> 00:23:09,420
Would you like that?

284
00:23:10,656 --> 00:23:14,158
And you haven't even

285
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:17,161
said anything
about how I look tonight.

286
00:23:29,675 --> 00:23:32,443
Men.

287
00:23:32,445 --> 00:23:35,746
You're all alike.

288
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:39,116
You are going
to pay for that.

289
00:23:39,118 --> 00:23:41,152
I thought
I was doing you a favor.

290
00:23:41,154 --> 00:23:44,121
Oh, you wanna
do me a favor.

291
00:23:44,123 --> 00:23:45,589
[LAUGHS]

292
00:23:46,993 --> 00:23:48,692
Fine.

293
00:23:48,694 --> 00:23:50,628
I got a job
for you tonight.

294
00:23:50,630 --> 00:23:53,664
A job?
You mean like work?

295
00:23:55,134 --> 00:23:56,667
I don't work.

296
00:23:56,669 --> 00:23:58,002
[BOTH LAUGHING]

297
00:23:58,004 --> 00:23:59,503
[ENGINE STARTS]

298
00:23:59,505 --> 00:24:00,905
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

299
00:24:09,081 --> 00:24:10,815
Hi, Mrs. Garrett.

300
00:24:10,817 --> 00:24:14,151
Gia Wilson,

301
00:24:14,153 --> 00:24:16,053
and Sarah Hayes.

302
00:24:16,055 --> 00:24:17,988
I remember you both.

303
00:24:19,892 --> 00:24:21,492
Please.

304
00:24:25,565 --> 00:24:26,964
Wow.

305
00:24:39,078 --> 00:24:40,711
Are you
going somewhere?

306
00:24:40,713 --> 00:24:42,112
Oh.

307
00:24:42,114 --> 00:24:44,815
You ran off so fast,
I forgot to tell you.

308
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:46,617
I have a date tonight.

309
00:24:46,619 --> 00:24:47,952
It's not a big deal.

310
00:24:47,954 --> 00:24:50,654
I should only be gone
a couple hours.

311
00:24:50,656 --> 00:24:52,656
- [LAUGHS] -That's
pretty fast for a woman

312
00:24:52,658 --> 00:24:55,893
who hasn't left a house
in over 15 years.

313
00:24:55,895 --> 00:24:58,596
I didn't say
it was a romantic date.

314
00:24:58,598 --> 00:25:00,898
[LAUGHS]
Heavens, no.

315
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:04,668
I gave up dating
those monsters years ago.

316
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:07,171
No, I am celibate
and content

317
00:25:07,173 --> 00:25:08,706
on remaining so.

318
00:25:08,708 --> 00:25:10,207
[LAUGHS]

319
00:25:10,209 --> 00:25:11,976
[NERVOUS LAUGHTER]

320
00:25:15,147 --> 00:25:17,848
I mostly need
some extra boxes

321
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:20,017
brought down
from the attic.

322
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:22,720
And I have more lights
I would like up outside,

323
00:25:22,722 --> 00:25:24,989
and I haven't done
any decorating

324
00:25:24,991 --> 00:25:27,258
in the bathrooms.

325
00:25:27,260 --> 00:25:30,194
There's plenty of food
in the fridge.

326
00:25:30,196 --> 00:25:32,196
And I would be insulted

327
00:25:32,198 --> 00:25:34,298
if you did not have

328
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:38,168
a glass
of my holiday eggnog

329
00:25:38,170 --> 00:25:40,137
before you left.

330
00:25:40,139 --> 00:25:42,840
No one makes it
quite like me.

331
00:25:42,842 --> 00:25:44,842
Oh, and before I leave,

332
00:25:44,844 --> 00:25:47,278
I need to show you
the door to the attic

333
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:50,214
where I keep
the extra decorations.

334
00:25:52,985 --> 00:25:55,586
Here are the stairs
to the attic.

335
00:25:59,158 --> 00:26:01,225
Is that Jaime's room?

336
00:26:04,230 --> 00:26:05,829
May I?

337
00:26:17,577 --> 00:26:19,944
Didn't I give this to Jamie
for Christmas one year?

338
00:26:21,581 --> 00:26:24,682
She loved this doll.

339
00:26:24,684 --> 00:26:27,718
Um, I always
wanted to know

340
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:30,120
why you never let Jaime
play with us outside.

341
00:26:30,122 --> 00:26:31,822
She always
looked so sad

342
00:26:31,824 --> 00:26:34,191
watching us
from her window.

343
00:26:34,193 --> 00:26:36,794
Jaime was very fragile.

344
00:26:38,230 --> 00:26:40,331
[MRS. GARRETT] I just
wanted to protect her.

345
00:26:40,333 --> 00:26:42,900
She needed protecting.

346
00:26:48,007 --> 00:26:50,975
They don't want to play
with you, baby.

347
00:26:50,977 --> 00:26:53,677
They are selfish
and spoiled rotten.

348
00:26:53,679 --> 00:26:56,013
They don't have
a good mama like you.

349
00:26:57,383 --> 00:27:00,250
Now, come away
from the window, baby.

350
00:27:00,252 --> 00:27:03,120
Stop torturing yourself.

351
00:27:03,122 --> 00:27:06,790
Those children,
they won't understand you.

352
00:27:06,792 --> 00:27:08,292
They will
make fun of you.

353
00:27:08,294 --> 00:27:10,728
They will laugh at you
because you are different.

354
00:27:14,867 --> 00:27:16,734
Do you hear me?

355
00:27:19,305 --> 00:27:22,006
Did you hear me?

356
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:26,844
What are you looking at?

357
00:27:38,791 --> 00:27:40,357
You see, baby?

358
00:27:40,359 --> 00:27:42,092
They don't want
to play with you.

359
00:27:43,996 --> 00:27:49,933
They ain't nothin' but a bunch
of naughty little children.

360
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:53,170
I always
tried to have

361
00:27:53,172 --> 00:27:56,240
a very positive attitude
around Jaime.

362
00:27:58,144 --> 00:28:01,145
I believe positive reinforcement
is very important

363
00:28:01,147 --> 00:28:03,013
for a child's
mental health.

364
00:28:05,051 --> 00:28:07,718
Thank you for opening
up to me about Jaime.

365
00:28:09,288 --> 00:28:11,822
It's nice to finally
understand why you and Jaime

366
00:28:11,824 --> 00:28:14,224
were so isolated
from everyone.

367
00:28:16,062 --> 00:28:19,063
I hope you don't
mind my asking...

368
00:28:19,065 --> 00:28:22,399
But what happened
to Jaime?

369
00:28:22,401 --> 00:28:25,102
There are so many
awful rumors.

370
00:28:25,104 --> 00:28:27,171
How did she go missing?

371
00:28:27,173 --> 00:28:28,806
[INHALES DEEPLY]

372
00:28:28,808 --> 00:28:32,276
That is a conversation
for another day, sweetie.

373
00:28:32,278 --> 00:28:34,311
I don't think
either of us

374
00:28:34,313 --> 00:28:37,314
needs to be dredging up
our painful pasts.

375
00:28:43,389 --> 00:28:47,091
Now, don't you girls
do anything too dangerous.

376
00:28:47,093 --> 00:28:48,792
Safety first.

377
00:28:48,794 --> 00:28:50,194
[CHUCKLES]

378
00:28:51,397 --> 00:28:53,864
I just can't
believe this.

379
00:28:53,866 --> 00:28:56,834
I remember seeing the three
of you playing in the street.

380
00:28:58,237 --> 00:29:01,071
And now look at you.

381
00:29:01,073 --> 00:29:04,842
Thank you
for your help.

382
00:29:17,289 --> 00:29:19,389
What-- come here.
Come look at this.

383
00:29:26,966 --> 00:29:29,967
Why would she screw
the windows shut?

384
00:29:29,969 --> 00:29:33,237
Well, I'm sure

385
00:29:33,239 --> 00:29:35,372
it's just for
added security.

386
00:29:35,374 --> 00:29:37,307
I mean,
she lives alone.

387
00:29:37,309 --> 00:29:39,409
That's debatable.

388
00:29:41,981 --> 00:29:43,313
I have to admit

389
00:29:43,315 --> 00:29:45,516
these mannequins
are kinda creeping me out.

390
00:29:47,219 --> 00:29:48,786
I say
we blow this joint.

391
00:29:48,788 --> 00:29:51,855
Oh, come on,
I cannot bail on her now.

392
00:29:51,857 --> 00:29:53,457
It's not just
the mannequins,

393
00:29:53,459 --> 00:29:55,125
they're strange,
Rachel. Come here.

394
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:56,527
I wanna show you
something else.

395
00:30:01,467 --> 00:30:04,535
All of these presents
are addressed to Jaime.

396
00:30:04,537 --> 00:30:06,403
Can you believe it?

397
00:30:06,405 --> 00:30:09,173
No one in their right mind
would do something like this.

398
00:30:09,175 --> 00:30:11,375
I don't know.

399
00:30:11,377 --> 00:30:13,377
Maybe it makes her
feel better.

400
00:30:13,379 --> 00:30:16,914
Or maybe she's just
cuckoo for cocoa puffs.

401
00:30:16,916 --> 00:30:19,917
- [LAUGHING] -Is it wrong for
her to hold onto the hope

402
00:30:19,919 --> 00:30:22,119
that Jaime might
come back some day?

403
00:30:22,121 --> 00:30:24,488
Come back?

404
00:30:24,490 --> 00:30:26,557
I thought
she was killed.

405
00:30:26,559 --> 00:30:29,927
Well, there have been
all kinds of crazy rumors.

406
00:30:29,929 --> 00:30:32,362
Who knows
what really happened.

407
00:30:32,364 --> 00:30:34,164
I know what happened.

408
00:30:35,467 --> 00:30:39,069
I was in kindergarten
and Jonathan Curtis

409
00:30:39,071 --> 00:30:41,371
who used to live down
this very street,

410
00:30:41,373 --> 00:30:44,074
said she was snatched
right out of her bed

411
00:30:44,076 --> 00:30:46,310
in the middle
of the night.

412
00:30:46,312 --> 00:30:48,278
And that's not all.

413
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,180
He said he knows
where she was taken.

414
00:30:50,182 --> 00:30:52,349
That she was taken
by some

415
00:30:52,351 --> 00:30:56,119
hideously deformed
creature named Krampus.

416
00:30:56,121 --> 00:30:58,455
What the hell is that?

417
00:30:58,457 --> 00:31:00,157
Don't listen to her.

418
00:31:00,159 --> 00:31:02,326
Krampus is just
an urban legend.

419
00:31:02,328 --> 00:31:05,863
That's what you think.

420
00:31:05,865 --> 00:31:08,365
Krampus is basically
like Santa Claus,

421
00:31:08,367 --> 00:31:10,367
but just
the exact opposite.

422
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:12,369
He kidnaps and tortures
little children

423
00:31:12,371 --> 00:31:14,972
who misbehave
during Christmas season.

424
00:31:14,974 --> 00:31:20,010
As if Santa
wasn't creepy enough.

425
00:31:20,012 --> 00:31:22,980
Hey, I was only five fucking years
old when he told me that story.

426
00:31:22,982 --> 00:31:24,281
He scared
the shit out of me.

427
00:31:24,283 --> 00:31:27,651
I had nightmares
for days ever since.

428
00:31:27,653 --> 00:31:32,122
Jonathan and Curtis
destroyed my childhood.

429
00:31:32,124 --> 00:31:35,626
Strange how you lost your
virginity to him in high school.

430
00:31:35,628 --> 00:31:37,394
I know, right?

431
00:31:44,036 --> 00:31:45,435
[SHOWER RUNNING]

432
00:31:47,573 --> 00:31:49,373
Honey?

433
00:31:55,414 --> 00:31:57,247
Thanks for leaving
the window open, sweetie.

434
00:31:57,249 --> 00:31:59,316
It's not cold
or anything.

435
00:32:23,142 --> 00:32:25,142
Babe.

436
00:32:25,144 --> 00:32:28,211
Are you gonna be feeling
frisky when you get out?

437
00:32:32,151 --> 00:32:35,352
Because once I start
reading...

438
00:32:38,457 --> 00:32:40,057
Fine by me.

439
00:32:50,703 --> 00:32:52,302
[GASPS]

440
00:33:00,145 --> 00:33:01,545
[THUMPING]

441
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,653
Ahh!

442
00:33:55,467 --> 00:33:56,800
Ugh!

443
00:33:56,802 --> 00:33:58,435
[GASPING]

444
00:33:58,437 --> 00:34:01,338
Oh, no, god!

445
00:34:01,340 --> 00:34:03,573
No, no!

446
00:34:03,575 --> 00:34:04,641
No!

447
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:06,343
No, please!

448
00:34:06,345 --> 00:34:07,744
Ahh!

449
00:34:07,746 --> 00:34:09,613
[MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

450
00:34:09,615 --> 00:34:12,115
♪... of the dear
savior's birth... ♪

451
00:34:16,789 --> 00:34:19,723
babe, you're totally
missing out on this shower.

452
00:34:20,793 --> 00:34:23,693
It's really warm.

453
00:34:23,695 --> 00:34:26,063
And I'm really wet.

454
00:34:26,065 --> 00:34:31,134
♪ ...he appeared
and the soul felt its worth ♪

455
00:34:31,136 --> 00:34:32,469
babe.

456
00:34:32,471 --> 00:34:34,571
Did you hear me?

457
00:34:34,573 --> 00:34:38,675
♪ A thrill of hope ♪

458
00:34:38,677 --> 00:34:43,447
♪ the weary world rejoices ♪

459
00:34:43,449 --> 00:34:51,121
♪ for yonder breaks
a new and glorious morn... ♪

460
00:34:51,123 --> 00:34:52,823
are you feeling
frisky tonight, babe?

461
00:34:52,825 --> 00:35:00,330
♪ Fall on your knees... ♪

462
00:35:01,467 --> 00:35:02,833
jeez.

463
00:35:13,545 --> 00:35:15,479
Hello, babe.

464
00:35:17,883 --> 00:35:19,483
What the fuck?

465
00:35:27,159 --> 00:35:29,593
Mandy!

466
00:35:29,595 --> 00:35:32,662
[SCREAMING]

467
00:35:34,333 --> 00:35:38,235
[WHIMPERS, SHOUTS]

468
00:35:46,478 --> 00:35:47,844
[WHIMPERS]

469
00:35:50,582 --> 00:35:52,382
[GURGLES]

470
00:36:20,946 --> 00:36:24,514
[RACHEL] Haven't you ever had
a strange collection before?

471
00:36:24,516 --> 00:36:28,218
Collections are just a waste
of time and money.

472
00:36:28,220 --> 00:36:30,887
Only boring people
who have nothing better to do

473
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:33,690
- collect things.
- Really?

474
00:36:33,692 --> 00:36:36,693
What about your collection
of beanie babies and STDS?

475
00:36:36,695 --> 00:36:38,295
[LAUGHS]

476
00:36:40,299 --> 00:36:42,299
If I'm gonna
survive this night,

477
00:36:42,301 --> 00:36:43,967
I'm gonna need
something better to sip on

478
00:36:43,969 --> 00:36:46,570
than old lady
watered-down eggnog.

479
00:36:46,572 --> 00:36:49,906
You could run down
to the shop 'n' stop.

480
00:36:49,908 --> 00:36:52,676
You have about ten minutes
until 12 o'clock.

481
00:36:53,612 --> 00:36:55,212
Okay.

482
00:37:03,455 --> 00:37:05,855
I have to try
this dress on.

483
00:37:05,857 --> 00:37:08,258
It's beautiful.

484
00:37:08,260 --> 00:37:10,260
I don't think
that's a good idea.

485
00:37:10,262 --> 00:37:11,595
I think
it's a great idea.

486
00:37:11,597 --> 00:37:14,598
This is going on
Facebook.

487
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:16,766
I thought
you were in a hurry.

488
00:37:16,768 --> 00:37:18,401
It'll take one second,
I swear.

489
00:37:18,403 --> 00:37:20,904
Make it fast.

490
00:37:20,906 --> 00:37:24,007
I'm gonna go get
the other boxes from the attic.

491
00:37:24,009 --> 00:37:25,709
[SQUEALS]

492
00:38:32,511 --> 00:38:33,843
- Gia.
- Ah!

493
00:38:33,845 --> 00:38:35,879
Look at this.

494
00:38:37,482 --> 00:38:38,982
So what?
Mrs. Garrett was a nurse.

495
00:38:38,984 --> 00:38:41,484
Big deal.

496
00:38:41,486 --> 00:38:43,386
How do I look?

497
00:38:43,388 --> 00:38:45,355
Uh, could you
forget that for one second?

498
00:38:45,357 --> 00:38:48,058
I'm serious.
Look at it.

499
00:38:48,060 --> 00:38:49,759
Read the name
of the person

500
00:38:49,761 --> 00:38:52,095
standing next
to Mrs. Garrett.

501
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:54,597
Laura Kimmel.

502
00:38:54,599 --> 00:38:56,333
My mother.

503
00:38:56,335 --> 00:38:57,901
Are you
fucking with me?

504
00:38:57,903 --> 00:38:59,569
Mrs. Garrett
lied to me.

505
00:38:59,571 --> 00:39:02,472
She told me that she
hardly knew my mother.

506
00:39:02,474 --> 00:39:05,008
Why do you think
she would say that?

507
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:07,010
I don't know.

508
00:39:07,012 --> 00:39:09,913
What would
she be hiding?

509
00:39:13,118 --> 00:39:16,820
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

510
00:39:16,822 --> 00:39:18,688
- [ABBY] Hello?
- [RACHEL] Grandma?

511
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:20,023
I need to ask you
something,

512
00:39:20,025 --> 00:39:22,892
and please
be honest with me.

513
00:39:22,894 --> 00:39:24,761
Well, of course,
honey.

514
00:39:24,763 --> 00:39:26,763
Did you know
that my mother

515
00:39:26,765 --> 00:39:28,932
and Mrs. Garrett
worked together?

516
00:39:28,934 --> 00:39:31,634
Were they friends?

517
00:39:31,636 --> 00:39:33,670
Why are you
asking me that?

518
00:39:33,672 --> 00:39:35,672
Just tell me.

519
00:39:35,674 --> 00:39:37,140
Rachel,

520
00:39:37,142 --> 00:39:40,110
[ABBY] Let's have this
conversation later.

521
00:39:41,713 --> 00:39:42,879
Where are you?

522
00:39:42,881 --> 00:39:44,848
- Please--
- [PHONE BEEPS]

523
00:39:44,850 --> 00:39:46,616
[MUSIC PLAYING]

524
00:40:26,525 --> 00:40:28,024
- Rah!
- Ah!

525
00:40:28,026 --> 00:40:30,126
Come here.

526
00:40:30,128 --> 00:40:32,028
Whoa.

527
00:40:32,030 --> 00:40:35,999
When you said Mrs. Garrett was
lonely, you weren't kidding.

528
00:40:36,001 --> 00:40:37,867
Oh, what's her deal?

529
00:40:37,869 --> 00:40:41,104
Well, she's certainly
not a people person.

530
00:40:43,041 --> 00:40:46,109
[SIGHS] Maybe they
make her feel safe.

531
00:40:48,447 --> 00:40:49,979
